article.headline: Hodges, Hoston score 25 points apiece
article.linkText: Tide never gets closer to LSU than 16 points
article.story:
TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) -- Doneeka Hodges and Scholanda Hoston
scored 25 points apiece, and No. 14 LSU routed Alabama 103-68
Thursday night.

Hoston was 10-of-14 from the field, and Hodges was 9-of-14 --
including 6-of-8 from 3-point range.

Seimone Augustus added 21 points for LSU (18-3, 6-1 Southeastern
Conference), while Temeka Johnson had 20.

Natasha Gamble led the Crimson Tide (10-11, 2-6) with 21 points.
Monique Bivins added 15 and Lauren Hill 12.

LSU never trailed and entered halftime with a 44-28 advantage.
The Tigers opened the second half on a 15-9 run, including a pair
of 3-pointers by Hodges.

The Tide got as close as 16 points in the second half on a
3-pointer by Hill, making it 53-37 with 17 minutes remaining.

Hoston's 3-pointer at the 1:22 mark put LSU in triple figures.
The Tigers hit 74 percent of their shots in the second half, and
finished at 65 percent.

Alabama was held to 43 percent shooting in the game, and let LSU
score 23 points off its 17 turnovers.
